\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
With the other women in the Group.  Because I also remember, I was very very nervous about public speaking.  I\rquote ve never liked public speaking, and I was being asked to give seminars and saying \'93No\'94
. And then finally I realised that I had to do one of these, so I decided I would accept an invitation \endash  I think it was Glasgow \endash 
 and, I mean, I really was very very worried about this, and I went to Glasgow to do it, and when I came back, the entire Women\rquote s Liberation Group met me at the airport!  (LAUGHS)  So sweet!  But I think that that the involvement in the Women
\rquote s Movement and the discovery that a lot of the problems that I had thought were my individual problems, were actually common to many women.  It was extremely important in enabling me to resist the likes of my supervisor, and actually d
o what I felt was the right thing to do - in terms of the work that I was doing. 
