\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Liz:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 Yes.  Okay
.  So if we could just think, now, about becoming a mother, and being at Bedford College, how did you decide to do that topic?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
That came very directly out of the Housework Study, because it became clear to me, during that \endash  the Housework Study \endash  that the point in women\rquote 
s lives where they really understood that conditions for women were very different from the conditions for men, was not the point of marriage - people got married in those days, they don\rquote t now - but it was the birth of a first child. Be
cause this introduced [inequality] - you can no longer pretend that you are equal.  Men, very much, in those days, left the child-rearing to the women.  I don\rquote t think it\rquote s hugely different now, but it\rquote 
s certainly different on the level of ideology and rhet
oric.  So I understood that it was the birth of the first child that was a turning point, and I had also begun to have some involvement in issues to do with healthcare, and I became quite fascinated by the ways in which the medicalisation of motherhood ha
d
 an impact on the whole social transition. So going back to the whole experience and notion of post-natal depression, I became very interested in how post-natal depression, as a cultural phenomenon, was created, where it had come from.  I spent quite a lo
n
g time looking at all the psychiatric medical literature, a lot of which, at the time, claimed that the reason why women became depressed after childbirth was because there was something wrong with them, and it was either something wrong with their orient
ation to femininity or there was something wrong with their hormones.  But they didn\rquote t have any evidence, it seemed to me.  And if you listened to women\rquote s accounts, that wasn\rquote t what they were saying.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Liz:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
So can you describe the design of that study? The methods used?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
Yes.  I selected a sample from one hospital in West London, which was universally and incorrectly assumed to be Hammersmith Hospital \endash  it\rquote s quite funny, actually, that!  I had started with a sample of 66 women, and set out to interview t
hem four times \endash 
 twice in pregnancy, and twice post-natally.  The final sample was 55 because some of the women had miscarriages, and moved and so on, so most of the analysis was done on 55 x 4 interviews.  And I was also present at a proportion of the bir
ths as well.  And all of that was preceded by nine months \endash  I don\rquote t know why it was nine months \endash 
 work, observing what happens at maternity hospitals, following doctors around in ante-natal clinics, sitting in the Labour Ward - and that work I never really published.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Liz:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
Which?  The observational bit?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
Mmm.  Because I wrote a paper on it, and showed it to Margot Jefferys - who worked at [Bedford] College - who was extremely rude about it!  (LAUGHS)  Extremely rude!
  And I put it in a drawer and never published it.  But there was also an issue about how to publish it, because quite frankly, a lot of what I heard and saw consisted of doctors being very arrogant and really quite nasty, and I didn\rquote 
t really know how to deal with it.  I mean, there are various things that I\rquote ve written where I\rquote ve used some of the encounters, but there weren\rquote 
t any examples, in the literature, of how to analyse this kind of thing.  You know, I had 906 accounts of doctor/patient \'85
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Liz:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 This i
s what fascinates me, because you mentioned, earlier, there was no kind of research training in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Liz:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
So was there any kind of help in how to analyse, ask questions \'85
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
No, no, no, no, no.  None.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Liz:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
Why was Jefferys critical?  Of what it was about?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
Well, I think probably because what I had written imposed a political analysis on this, which \endash  I\rquote m sure I didn\rquote t use the word \'93patriarchy\'94 at the time \endash  but I remember using a phrase, \'93intra-uterine neo-colonialism
