\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Liz:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
Did you feel that you were a Feminist doing research, at that stage?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Liz:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
How would you have described it, then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
Described what?  My research?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Liz:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
I thought I was redressing an imbalance in the research.  Most of it had been from a masculine point of vi
ew, and had reflected - the vast bulk of sociology was about these really important issues to do with power (LAUGHS) and occupation, and social class defined in male terms, and there was simply an enormous gap.  You didn\rquote 
t have to call yourself a Feminist 
in order to do that, any more than the men who did the rest of it called themselves Masculinist.  It was simply something that needed to be done.  And the way in which people talk about Feminists and Feminism is always to imply that people who identify th
emselves as Feminists are, in some sense, biased, and, of course, they\rquote re no more biased than people who aren\rquote 
t Feminist.  But I think a lot of my research and writing has been informed by my desire to put women back on the centre stage along with men.  But
 a lot of it has also been on a more general level about the uses of research to inform public policy, and women are recipients of public policy just as men are.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Liz:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 Do you feel you
\rquote ve been labelled at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 Oh, I\rquote 
m always labelled!  I\rquote m labelled as a biased Feminist, qualitative researcher, or somebody who underwent some very strange conversion to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid9911662  randomised controlled trials \endash }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643  you know, I must have been brainwashed by some medic at some point.  There are a whole lot of stories about all of this tha
t I think are quite funny really!  But they reflect people\rquote s needs, it seems to me, to stereotype and to put people in categories, and to attach labels, and I don\rquote t particularly like having labels attached to me.  I think it\rquote 
s actually unhelpful.  It\rquote s unhelpful in terms of the task of understanding \endash  which is what you\rquote re trying to do in this interview \endash  trying to understand where somebody is coming from, and why they\rquote 
re doing what they do.  Getting labels out of the way is part of the process of understanding what actually someone\rquote s life is all about, isn\rquote t it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Liz:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
Yes.  But I suppose I\rquote m interested in what it was like for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
, with those labels, and some of the arguments that have gone on \'85
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
Well, I used to get disturbed by them, and I used to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid9911662  get irritated, but I don\rquote t any}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
more, because I think, these are problems that belong to other people!  (LAUGHS)  And the older you get, the less concerned you get by all of that, and the more you just think, \'93Well, I\rquote m going to go on doing what I think is 
the right thing to do\'94.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Liz:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
Do you feel, though, that there was a sense, in the earlier Feminism, about pioneering different agendas for research, different ways of doing research?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 Oh yes.  Yes.  And it
\rquote s interesting, one of the things that I\rquote ve written which is the most quoted, is this chapter in the book edited by Helen Roberts, called, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
Doing Feminist Research}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643  [1981] \endash  which is the [chapter] on interviewing women, which she asked me to write!  I never w
ould have written it otherwise.  And it provoked quite a lot of discussion in the literature, quite a lot of it quite critical, which I think is good, because the whole point about doing something and saying something is you want people to engage with it 
and point out where it was that you were wrong.  But I found that interesting, and I suppose one doesn\rquote t like to look back and think that what one does was pioneering.  But actually, it was pioneering, but I didn\rquote 
t see it as pioneering at the time, I just felt I was being bloody-minded and doing things that people didn\rquote t want me to do!  (LAUGHS)  \tab You know, the danger of that is that the more people don\rquote 
t want you to do things, the more you think, \'93Well, I\rquote m going to anyway!\'94  (LAUGHS)  I think I\rquote ve been an uncomfortable person to have in a university, and I think that this place has really never known what to do with me, but they
\rquote ve learnt, on the whole, to leave me alone.  And also, of course, my contribution to what used to be called the Research Assessment Exercise has been quite high because of the publications and grants as well, so I\rquote 
ve been convenient in that sense.  But I\rquote ve not been a mainstream player in any of the internal University politics, because I decided that life was too short to do all of that, and it isn\rquote t what people get remembered for - you don\rquote 
t get remembered for going to meetings of the Committee of Professors, and meetings of this and that.  You might get an increase in your salary, as a consequence but you won\rquote t get much else.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Liz:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
And just before we leave Feminism, some views perhaps about where it\rquote s gone more recently?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 Well, it\rquote 
s going to come back, because it always does.  Look at the long history of how Feminist Movements, or Women\rquote s Movements, or whatever you want to call
 them, come and go.  But it was Juliet Mitchell who said the possibility of women revolting, in a sense, is always there.  It\rquote 
s always there.  But it takes a constellation of particular circumstances to bring it to the surface in the form of some kind of organised Movement.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Liz:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 Yes.  I guess I
\rquote m thinking more in terms of academia really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 Oh well, I mean what
\rquote s happened, you look at all these indices of what\rquote s happened to women and equality since the 1970s, and yes, there have been changes, and yes, 
the gender gap in earnings and distribution of women and men in occupations is less than it was, but it\rquote 
s still pretty pronounced, including in this institution.  When I gave my inaugural lecture here, I got hold of some figures about gender and grades and salaries in this institution.  I didn\rquote 
t say it was this institution, but I put a Power Point slide up with the figures.  I said, \'93An anonymous institution not very far from here,\'94 and the Director who was sitting in front of me at the time, just didn\rquote t know where to look!
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Liz:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
But I think I think I\rquote ve read that you were saying that, initially, in research, Feminists look to those sorts of statistics to be able to say, \'93This is our situation\'94, but now, when we have multiple constructive realities and so on
 - not particularly \'93we\'94, but some researchers believe that, that they could absolutely turn their back on statistical evidence, if you like.  And I just wondered how you felt about some of the post-Modern Feminists?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 I don\rquote 
t have much time for them (LAUGHS) in the sense that, I feel, to me, Feminism has always been a matter of evidence, and the evidence is that this is the major - well, apart from class, and, of course, there\rquote 
s a very close connection between class and women - this is the major access of differentiation and discrimination, and remains so.  And it\rquote s there.  I mean, why would you turn your back on it?  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Liz:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
I do sometimes wonder the extent to which some of the post-Modern writing has made it very difficult for another generation of people to actually do research \'85
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Liz:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \'85
 because Clive Seale argues that that it\rquote s ended up causing paralysis.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
I think so.  No, no, no, I think that\rquote s right.  But isn\rquote t that what we were talking about earlier?  What is the point of being
 an academic, or the point of research engaging in these theoretical debates, which are going to be ultimately arid in terms of having any impact outside that world of ideas and theory?  If you think that\rquote s the point of it, then that\rquote 
s what you do, you write these things which your colleagues in the post-Modernist world read, but that is about all.  I\rquote ve always wanted to reach a wider audience, I\rquote 
ve always wanted to have an impact outside the world of research and universities, but I haven\rquote t got the disposition to be a political activist, and I think we all need to do what it is that we\rquote re best at doing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Liz:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
Yes.  Can I use that as a link to my final interest which is alternative ways of writing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 Oh yes. Yes.
