d like to ask you something a bit provocative in the sense of some developments \endash  not yours, but other people doing this, where they\rquote ve deliberately tried to blur the genres. I mean some people argue there\rquote 
s no difference between journalism and research, I mean, how do you feel about that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 Well, 
there is a difference between journalism and research.  When you\rquote re writing a research report, you constantly have to refer back to the data.  Am I being fair to the data?  When you\rquote re writing a novel, you don\rquote 
t have to do that, what you have to refer to is the authenticity of the characters. Sometimes the characters won\rquote t allow you, as the author, to say something that you want to say, or they won\rquote t do what you want them to do, but that\rquote 
s very different.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Liz:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 But do you think it
\rquote s important that the audience knows which is being written at that time?
