\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 Yes.  I\rquote 
m doing a systematic review at the moment of the transition to motherhood, and an amazing number of those studies draw on interviews with one or two or three people and the researchers make prono
uncements on the basis of these very small number of narratives.  I mean, in what sense are those conclusions that they\rquote re drawing fiction, and in what sense are they fact?  Do you see what I mean?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Liz:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 So, for you, it
\rquote s the number of cases, or how the sample is drawn?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
Those things are important.  I\rquote m not saying that you can\rquote t learn something very valuable from in-depth narratives from a few people \endash  you can \endash  but I think it\rquote 
s a matter of what you say on the basis of that: if you put in almost the whole of the narratives that people have told, then other people can judge them themselves.  If you [put in] selected quotes, and say, \'93This means X\'94, and \'93This means Y\'94
, then what is the status of that kind of conclusion?  I provoke people by saying, \'93Well, what\rquote s the difference between fact and fiction?\'94 but I\rquote m trying to make people think about it.
