Not particularly, no.  That was quite funny actually!  The origin of that is that Ursula [Owen] at Virago was trying to get me to write all sorts of things about women at the time, and I said, \'93No, I only want to write a novel\'94
, and she sent me a contract for a novel, the next day, which I thought was so brave!  I sold the world rights at for \'a3750. That was the book that I could have made money out of, and I never did!  You know, my novels are not great literature, they
