t.  I wanted them to not to end up as drug addicts on the streets!  (LAUGHS)  Well, obvi
ously I wanted them to be happy.  Both my daughters did social science, although I tried very hard to prevent them from doing that. One of them went into the film and media world, and is now working at the University of the Arts, running film and media co
urses, and she has quite a distinguished career in the media world.  But she did Social and Political Science at Cambridge, and she has a Ph.D. on the role of angels in Hollywood films \endash 
 extraordinary!  The other daughter did Sociology at LSE, and then did a Masters in Public Health at the School of Hygiene, and is now finishing her Ph.D..  I think it\rquote 
s very bizarre, actually. My son did engineering and then did an MBA, and works in marketing.
