\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Liz:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
Why did you try and prevent your daughters from doing social science?  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid5071929\charrsid5071929 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16731643\charrsid16731643 
Well, because I think it\rquote s quite a difficult life, and it\rquote s more difficult in the sense that research funding is more difficult to get \endash  and perhaps it should be.  Most of my life has been in the contract research world, and I don
\rquote t think there have been huge changes in the position of contract researchers over that time.  I mean, it\rquote s better, there\rquote s more equality, but on the whole, contract researchers are treated as second class citizens.
