\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid3293087 Ann:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid6309058\charrsid2046902 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid6309058\charrsid2046902 
Actually, I think it was the opposite.  [The chapter] was partly a reflection on ordinary discourse between people being therapeutic in ways that psychiatrists claim for what they do. So it was actually positioned more in the anti-psychiatry movement!

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid6309058\charrsid2046902 PAUL:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid6309058\charrsid2046902 
(LAUGHS)  But you say you attack the conventional method in terms of it reducing women to the status of children, and there\rquote s that kind of psychological stuff... 
